title: Y-The Last Man [ _o,O:MfX:O.o_]
description:
Y: The Last Man

Complete Run

On July 17, 2002, something (referred to as a plague) simultaneously kills every mammal possessing a Y chromosome - including embryos, fertilized eggs, and even sperm. The only exceptions appear to be Yorick Brown, a young amateur escape artist, and his Capuchin monkey Ampersand.


IMHO, one of the best comics ever made. I enjoyed reading it, and was really glad that I did afterward. Yet again, not my scans, but figured the old interwebs could use more good comics, and full series at that. Took me forever to find these.

_o.O:MfX:O.o_
